{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' infra/compose/docker-compose.yml\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "services:\n  backend:\n    build:\n      context: ../../backend\n    working_dir: /app\n    volumes:\n      - ../../backend:/app\n    environment:\n      PYTHONDONTWRITEBYTECODE: \"1\"\n      PYTHONUNBUFFERED: \"1\"\n    ports:\n      - \"8565:8565\"\n    command: uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8565\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - python\n        - -c\n        - |\n          import sys, urllib.request\n          urllib.request.urlopen(\"http://127.0.0.1:8565/api/hello\")\n          sys.exit(0)\n      interval: 5s\n      timeout: 5s\n      retries: 20\n      start_period: 5s\n\n  frontend:\n    build:\n      context: ../../frontend\n    depends_on:\n      backend:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    working_dir: /app\n    environment:\n      CHOKIDAR_USEPOLLING: \"true\"\n      VITE_DEV_PROXY_TARGET: http://backend:8565\n    volumes:\n      - ../../frontend:/app\n      - /app/node_modules\n    ports:\n      - \"8566:8566\"\n    command: npm run dev -- --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8566\n    healthcheck:\n      test:\n        - CMD\n        - node\n        - -e\n        - |\n          require(\"http\").get(\"http://127.0.0.1:8566\", (response) => {\n            process.exit(response.statusCode === 200 ? 0 : 1);\n          }).on(\"error\", () => process.exit(1));\n      interval: 5s\n      timeout: 5s\n      retries: 20\n      start_period: 10s\n\n  browser:\n    build:\n      context: ../../tools/webapp-qa\n    depends_on:\n      frontend:\n        condition: service_healthy\n    working_dir: /workspace/tools/webapp-qa\n    environment:\n      PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH: /usr/bin/chromium\n      TARGET_BASE_URL: http://frontend:8566\n    volumes:\n      - ../../:/workspace\n      - webapp_qa_node_modules:/workspace/tools/webapp-qa/node_modules\n    command: sleep infinity\n\nvolumes:\n  webapp_qa_node_modules:\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' infra/compose/docker-compose.yml\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_17", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 38, "prompt_index": 3, "prompt_name": "02 \u2014 Scaffold the React Frontend with Vite", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T21:08:09-07:00"}
{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "I have enough context to commit to an approach: replace the placeholder JSX app with a proper Vite TypeScript scaffold, keep the current dev port and proxy behavior, add lint/format scripts, and give the landing route a branded sessions-...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_18", "text": "I have enough context to commit to an approach: replace the placeholder JSX app with a proper Vite TypeScript scaffold, keep the current dev port and proxy behavior, add lint/format scripts, and give the landing route a branded sessions-first shell that matches the product direction without pre-building real flows.\n\nPlan:\n1. Generate or align to the current Vite React TypeScript baseline, then adapt it to the repo\u2019s existing port, Docker, and proxy setup.\n2. Introduce a minimal typed app structure with a route shell, placeholder home screen, and project-branded styling.\n3. Add frontend quality tooling for linting and formatting, plus any TypeScript config needed for a stricter foundation.\n4. Run targeted verification: install deps, lint, build, start the app, and do browser-based visual QA with a screenshot.\n5. Write the required reviewer summary file as the final action.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 39, "prompt_index": 3, "prompt_name": "02 \u2014 Scaffold the React Frontend with Vite", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T21:08:18-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f", "event_type": "Command Started", "message": "in progress: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "exit_code": null, "id": "item_19", "status": "in_progress", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.started"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 40, "prompt_index": 3, "prompt_name": "02 \u2014 Scaffold the React Frontend with Vite", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T21:08:19-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0\ufe0f", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "---\nname: webapp-qa\ndescription: Use when interacting with a local webapp in this repo, taking screenshots, and verifying behavior both visually and functionally through the docker-compose dev stack and the bundled Puppeteer runner.\n---\n\n# Webapp QA\n\nUse this skill when the task involves running the local app, exercising it in a browser, taking screenshots, or checking that UI behavior and rendered output match expectations.\n\n## Workflow\n\n1. Start the local stack with `docker compose up -d --build`.\n2. Confirm the app is healthy with `docker compose ps`.\n3. Run browser checks from the `browser` service with `docker compose run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec <spec-path>`.\n4. Review the generated screenshot under `.artifacts/webapp-qa/`.\n\n## App URLs\n\n- From the host machine, the app is available at `http://localhost:8566`.\n- From inside the browser container, use `http://frontend:8566`.\n\n## Puppeteer Specs\n\nThe reusable runner lives at `tools/webapp-qa/scripts/run-spec.mjs`.\n\nSpecs are JSON files with this shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"url\": \"http://frontend:8566\",\n  \"outputPath\": \"/workspace/.artifacts/webapp-qa/example.png\",\n  \"viewport\": { \"width\": 1440, \"height\": 960 },\n  \"steps\": [\n    { \"action\": \"waitForSelector\", \"selector\": \"[data-testid='app-card']\" },\n    { \"action\": \"assertText\", \"text\": \"Hello from FastAPI!\" },\n    { \"action\": \"screenshot\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nSupported actions:\n\n- `goto`\n- `waitForSelector`\n- `waitForText`\n- `click`\n- `type`\n- `press`\n- `hover`\n- `assertSelector`\n- `assertText`\n- `assertUrlIncludes`\n- `waitForTimeout`\n- `screenshot`\n\n## Example\n\nUse `tools/webapp-qa/examples/homepage.spec.json` for a basic smoke test plus screenshot:\n\n```bash\ndocker compose run --rm browser npm run check -- --spec ./examples/homepage.spec.json\n```\n\n## Verification Guidance\n\n- For functional checks, prefer explicit `assertText`, `assertSelector`, and URL assertions over informal observation.\n- For visual checks, capture a screenshot after the page reaches the expected stable state.\n- If a page depends on backend data, verify the user-visible result instead of only checking network readiness.\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,240p' /Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.codex/skills/webapp-qa/SKILL.md\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_19", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 41, "prompt_index": 3, "prompt_name": "02 \u2014 Scaffold the React Frontend with Vite", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-03-31T21:08:19-07:00"}
